The paper introduces a new class of DPPs and applies it to the problem of change-point detection. The paper's focus is on efficient MAP inference, which is a common problem in machine learning and optimization, suggesting that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The application of the proposed method to change-point detection suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.ST (Statistics). Finally, the paper's use of determinantal point processes and subset selection suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory).
